This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of biological membranes in electron microscopy images. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed pruning method for CNNs indicates that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of real-time performance suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
